SIMPLE: hydroxy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydroxy-
<hw>Hy*drox"y-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A combining
form, also used adjectively, indicating <xex>hydroxyl</xex> as an
ingredient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hydroxy acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>an organic
acid, having (besides the hydroxyl group of the carboxyl radical) an
alcoholic hydroxyl group, and thus having the qualities of an alcohol in
addition to its acid properties; as, lactic and tartaric acids are
<xex>hydroxy</xex> acids.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydroxyl</ent>⟦br⟧
